Melania Trump will be participating in the 2018 International Women of Courage Celebration on March 21st. She will give remarks and present the International Women of Courage Award to a group of women who have shown tremendous courage and leadership in advocating for women's rights around the world. The IWOC Award, which began in 2007, honors over 120 women from more than 65 countries who have overcome challenges while supporting the advancement of women. Melania Trump expressed admiration for these women and their fight for equality and freedom, stating that their courage strengthens her belief in the power of women's solidarity and support. She considers it a privilege to stand with these women and present them with the awards they deserve.